{
  "text": "The cutoff frequency relative to Nyquist frequency for the Hamming filter [CITATION_1] was varied for every run of the 2-D FBP algorithm. The result is shown in figure 3a . As one can see the optimal value for the cutoff frequency is 0.15, where the average MSE has the lowest value (33.5352). The OE reconstruction method was tested by varying the number of iterations. The result is shown in figure 3b . The minimum value for the average MSE (109.21) corresponds to the image reconstructed after 20 iterations. The number of iterations was also varied for the OSEM reconstruction. Each time 2 subsets were used. The resulting bias, variance and average MSE are shown in figure 3c . The average MSE shows a minimum value (76.84) for 2 iterations. Finally, the LM-OSEM algorithm was tested varying number of iterations and using 2 subsets for each run. The result is shown in figure 3d . The minimum average MSE has a value 29.7853 for 4 iterations. The images obtained with optimal parameters for each of the algorithms are shown in figure 4.",
  "citation_candidates": [
